title: MS in Program Evaluation and Data Analytics
B.S., Public Service and Public Policy
Research Analyst
description_1: Coordinates and assists with data collection activities for assigned research initiatives; prepares data collection materials as needed.
description_2: Develops dashboards and maintains databases used to collect and archive data for research initiatives.
description_3: Partner with peers to establish, evaluate, and continually improve measurement methodologies, while adhering to analytic and reporting standards.

title: Research Specialist
description_1: Managed databases for $4.7M COVID-19 Project, which included reliable data entry, project development, participant tracking and data verification as well as coordinating data analysis activities and submitting data to external entities.
description_2: Assisted in the design and implementation of statistical techniques and computer data systems including establishing coding formats for future scientific data collection for both quantitative and qualitative research.
description_3: Coordinated the development of research activities and modification of questionnaires or other data collection or sampling instruments or data summarization methods, procedures or reporting formats.

title: Research Aide
description_1: Maintained cross-departmental relationships by partnering with Oxford University and ARTIS International to create a civic education initiative known as the Quill Project that will allow citizens and scholars to better understand Arizona’s contribution to constitutional democracy.
description_2: Conducted and coded in-depth analysis of The Records of the Arizona Constitutional Convention and the Minutes of the Convention which includes propositions, debates, and report decisions onto a digitial repository.
description_3: Presented the Quill Project to state legislators, university staff and faculty at the Arizona State Capitol.
